Now that we know who's in the world series we can predict between the Astros and the Phillies. The Astros in stats and players have an overall better team than the Phillies, but the Phillies have surprised everyone by winning against both the Braves and the Padres. The Phillies are still lacking against the Astros due to their weak defense and being carried by harper. Given that, I wouldn't be shocked to see a close fight between both of them but I wouldn't be surprised to see the Astros sweeping as well. It's pretty much done if the Phillies don't win or have close fights while in Houston. After the first two games, it'll be clear who has a chance of winning the world series. My prediction is supported by the odds as it says on AS, "According to the odds, the Astros are at a line of -170, while the Philadelphia team is at +143 to win the Major League trophy this season."
I’d probably take 10:1 odds on the Astros sweeping it at this point. The Phillies look hot, but I don’t think that will be enough
